  "response": "Both online and print NCERT books have their advantages for UPSC CSE preparation. Here's a comparison:\n\nPrint NCERT Books:\nPros:\n- Better for detailed reading\n- No digital distractions\n- Easy to highlight and make notes\n- More comfortable for long reading sessions\n- Can be carried anywhere\n- Easier to refer back and revise\n\nOnline NCERT Books:\nPros:\n- Free and easily accessible\n- Can be read on multiple devices\n- Searchable content\n- Digital bookmarking\n- Lightweight and convenient\n- Can use digital highlighters\n\nRecommendation:\n1. If possible, use both formats\n2. Purchase physical books for core subjects\n3. Use online versions for quick reference\n4. Choose based on personal learning style\n5. Complement with other study materials\n\nOverall, print books are generally recommended for serious UPSC CSE preparation due to better comprehension and note-making capabilities. However, online resources can be a good supplementary tool.",
